The state of Nicaragua is a federated republic that is also known by some of its other names like the Republic of Nicaragua or just the Republic. Nicaragua shares its borders with 5 other countries and they are Honduras in the north, Costa Rica in the south, Columbia in the Southeast, Panamá in the northwestern part and by the Pacific Ocean in the west. The total area of the Republic of Nicaragua is estimated to be 129,494 square kilometers that features sea lid area of 7,600 square kilometers which makes up 13.4 percent of the total land area of Nicaragua. The territorial claims of the country has been significant but none of these claims have been recognized to date.
